---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import LegalLayout from '../components/LegalLayout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | AUXO Data Labs"
  description="Learn how AUXO Data Labs collects, uses, and protects your personal information in compliance with UAE PDPL and GDPR."
>
  <div class="pt-24 pb-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <LegalLayout
        title="Privacy Policy"
        lastUpdated="January 15, 2025"
        effectiveDate="January 1, 2025"
        summary="This Privacy Policy explains how AUXO Data Labs collects, uses, protects, and shares your personal information when you use our website and services. We are committed to transparency and compliance with UAE PDPL, GDPR, and international data protection standards."
      >
        <!-- Introduction -->
        <div class="mb-8 p-6 bg-lime-400/5 border border-lime-400/20 rounded-lg">
          <h2 class="!mt-0">Introduction</h2>
          <p>
            AUXO Data Labs ("we," "our," "us," or "Company") is a data analytics consultancy based in Dubai, United Arab Emirates. We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains our practices regarding the collection, use, disclosure, and protection of personal data in compliance with:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>UAE Federal Decree-Law No. 45 of 2021</strong> on the Protection of Personal Data (UAE PDPL)</li>
            <li><strong>EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)</strong> where applicable</li>
            <li>International data protection best practices</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            By using our website or engaging our services, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2>1. Data Controller Information</h2>
        <p><strong>Data Controller:</strong> AUXO Data Labs</p>
        <p><strong>Location:</strong> Dubai, United Arab Emirates</p>
        <p><strong>Contact for Privacy Matters:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Email: privacy@auxodata.ae</li>
          <li>General Contact: hello@auxodata.ae</li>
          <li>Website: <a href={`${base}contact`}>Contact Form</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>

        <h3>2.1 Personal Information You Provide</h3>
        <p>We collect personal information that you voluntarily provide when you:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Contact Us:</strong> Name, email address, phone number, company name, job title, message content</li>
          <li><strong>Request Services:</strong> Project requirements, budget information, timeline preferences, technical specifications</li>
          <li><strong>Subscribe to Newsletter:</strong> Email address, communication preferences</li>
          <li><strong>Use Our Assessment Tools:</strong> Company size, industry, data maturity information, business challenges</li>
          <li><strong>Attend Events/Webinars:</strong> Registration details, professional information</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2.2 Information Automatically Collected</h3>
        <p>When you visit our website, we automatically collect certain information through cookies and similar technologies:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> IP address, browser type and version, operating system, device identifiers</li>
          <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Pages visited, time spent on pages, navigation paths, referring URLs, exit pages</li>
          <li><strong>Technical Data:</strong> Language preferences, screen resolution, timezone, cookie data</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics Data:</strong> Aggregated usage statistics, user behavior patterns, conversion metrics</li>
        </ul>
        <p>For detailed information about our use of cookies, please see our <a href={`${base}cookie-policy`}>Cookie Policy</a>.</p>

        <h3>2.3 Information from Third Parties</h3>
        <p>We may receive information about you from:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>LinkedIn:</strong> Professional profile information (with your consent)</li>
          <li><strong>Business Partners:</strong> Referral information from trusted partners</li>
          <li><strong>Public Sources:</strong> Publicly available business information for B2B purposes</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Legal Basis for Processing (UAE PDPL & GDPR)</h2>
        <p>We process your personal data based on the following legal grounds:</p>

        <h3>3.1 Consent</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Marketing communications (you can withdraw consent at any time)</li>
          <li>Non-essential cookies and tracking technologies</li>
          <li>Newsletter subscriptions</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.2 Contractual Necessity</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Processing service requests and consultations</li>
          <li>Delivering contracted services</li>
          <li>Billing and payment processing</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.3 Legitimate Interests</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Website analytics and improvements</li>
          <li>Fraud prevention and security</li>
          <li>Business development and networking</li>
          <li>Direct marketing to existing clients (B2B)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.4 Legal Obligations</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Compliance with UAE tax and accounting laws</li>
          <li>Responding to legal requests and court orders</li>
          <li>Regulatory compliance requirements</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use your personal information for the following purposes:</p>

        <h3>4.1 Service Delivery</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Responding to inquiries and consultation requests</li>
          <li>Providing data analytics and consultancy services</li>
          <li>Delivering project deliverables and reports</li>
          <li>Client communication and project management</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>4.2 Business Operations</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Billing, invoicing, and payment processing</li>
          <li>Contract management and legal compliance</li>
          <li>Quality assurance and service improvement</li>
          <li>Internal record-keeping and auditing</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>4.3 Marketing and Communications</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Sending newsletters and industry insights (with consent)</li>
          <li>Promoting our services and events</li>
          <li>Conducting market research and surveys</li>
          <li>Personalized service recommendations</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>4.4 Website Improvement</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Analyzing website usage and performance</li>
          <li>Optimizing user experience and navigation</li>
          <li>Testing new features and functionality</li>
          <li>Security monitoring and threat detection</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Information Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
        <p><strong>We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information.</strong> We may share your information in the following circumstances:</p>

        <h3>5.1 Service Providers</h3>
        <p>We engage trusted third-party service providers who assist with:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Cloud Hosting:</strong> AWS, Microsoft Azure (data storage and processing)</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> Google Analytics (website performance tracking)</li>
          <li><strong>Communication:</strong> Email service providers for newsletters</li>
          <li><strong>Payment Processing:</strong> Secure payment gateways</li>
          <li><strong>CRM Systems:</strong> Client relationship management</li>
        </ul>
        <p>All service providers are contractually obligated to protect your data and use it only for specified purposes.</p>

        <h3>5.2 Business Partners</h3>
        <p>With your consent, we may share information with technology partners or implementation partners for joint service delivery.</p>

        <h3>5.3 Legal Requirements</h3>
        <p>We may disclose your information when required by law or to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Comply with legal obligations, court orders, or regulatory requests</li>
          <li>Protect our rights, property, or safety</li>
          <li>Detect, prevent, or address fraud or security issues</li>
          <li>Enforce our Terms and Conditions</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>5.4 Business Transfers</h3>
        <p>In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred to the acquiring entity, subject to this Privacy Policy.</p>

        <h2>6. International Data Transfers</h2>
        <p>As a UAE-based company serving international clients, your data may be transferred to and processed in:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>United Arab Emirates</strong> (primary data location)</li>
          <li><strong>European Union</strong> (cloud infrastructure)</li>
          <li><strong>United States</strong> (certain service providers)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>When transferring data outside the UAE, we ensure appropriate safeguards through:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs)</strong> approved by the EU Commission</li>
          <li><strong>Adequacy Decisions:</strong> Transfers to countries with adequate data protection</li>
          <li><strong>Binding Corporate Rules:</strong> For multinational service providers</li>
          <li><strong>Explicit Consent:</strong> When required by law</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Data Security</h2>
        <p>We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your personal information:</p>

        <h3>7.1 Technical Measures</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> TLS/SSL encryption for data in transit, AES-256 encryption for data at rest</li>
          <li><strong>Access Controls:</strong> Role-based access, multi-factor authentication, principle of least privilege</li>
          <li><strong>Network Security:</strong> Firewalls, intrusion detection systems, regular security audits</li>
          <li><strong>Secure Development:</strong> Code reviews, vulnerability assessments, penetration testing</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>7.2 Organizational Measures</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Employee training on data protection and security</li>
          <li>Confidentiality agreements with all personnel</li>
          <li>Regular security policy reviews and updates</li>
          <li>Incident response and breach notification procedures</li>
          <li>Annual third-party security assessments</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Important:</strong> While we take all reasonable precautions, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

        <h2>8. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>We retain your personal information only as long as necessary for the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy:</p>

        <table class="w-full my-6 text-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-zinc-700">
              <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-lime-400">Data Type</th>
              <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-lime-400">Retention Period</th>
              <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-lime-400">Reason</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Contact Form Submissions</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">2 years from last contact</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Business development</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Client Project Data</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">7 years post-project</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Legal, tax, warranty obligations</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Marketing Consent</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Until consent withdrawn</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Ongoing communications</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Website Analytics</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">26 months (Google Analytics)</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Website improvement</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Financial Records</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">7 years minimum</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">UAE tax law compliance</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p>After the retention period expires, we securely delete or anonymize your data unless longer retention is required by law.</p>

        <h2>9. Your Rights Under UAE PDPL and GDPR</h2>
        <p>You have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p>

        <h3>9.1 Right of Access</h3>
        <p>Request a copy of the personal data we hold about you, including details about processing activities.</p>

        <h3>9.2 Right to Rectification</h3>
        <p>Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete personal data.</p>

        <h3>9.3 Right to Erasure ("Right to be Forgotten")</h3>
        <p>Request deletion of your personal data when:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>It's no longer necessary for the original purpose</li>
          <li>You withdraw consent (where consent was the legal basis)</li>
          <li>You object to processing and there are no overriding legitimate grounds</li>
          <li>Data was unlawfully processed</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>9.4 Right to Restriction of Processing</h3>
        <p>Request temporary limitation on how we use your data in certain circumstances.</p>

        <h3>9.5 Right to Data Portability</h3>
        <p>Receive your personal data in a structured, commonly used, machine-readable format and transfer it to another controller.</p>

        <h3>9.6 Right to Object</h3>
        <p>Object to processing based on legitimate interests or for direct marketing purposes.</p>

        <h3>9.7 Right to Withdraw Consent</h3>
        <p>Withdraw consent at any time (where consent is the legal basis for processing).</p>

        <h3>9.8 Right to Lodge a Complaint</h3>
        <p>File a complaint with the relevant supervisory authority:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>UAE:</strong> UAE Data Office (when operational)</li>
          <li><strong>EU:</strong> Your local data protection authority (if GDPR applies)</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="my-8 p-6 bg-zinc-800 border border-zinc-700 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="!mt-0">How to Exercise Your Rights</h3>
          <p>To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@auxodata.ae">privacy@auxodata.ae</a></li>
            <li>Subject Line: "Data Subject Rights Request"</li>
            <li>Include: Your full name, contact details, and description of your request</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>Response Time:</strong> We will respond within 30 days of receiving your request. For complex requests, we may extend this by an additional 60 days with notification.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>10. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Our services are designed for businesses and professionals. We do not knowingly collect personal information from individuals under 18 years of age. If we become aware that we have inadvertently collected data from a child, we will take immediate steps to delete such information.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Third-Party Links</h2>
        <p>
          Our website may contain links to third-party websites (e.g., LinkedIn, Twitter, partner sites). We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these external sites. We encourage you to review their privacy policies before providing any personal information.
        </p>

        <h2>12. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect changes in our practices, technologies, legal requirements, or business operations. Significant changes will be communicated through:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Prominent notice on our website</li>
          <li>Email notification to registered users (where applicable)</li>
          <li>Updated "Last Updated" date at the top of this policy</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Your continued use of our services after changes take effect constitutes acceptance of the updated Privacy Policy.</p>

        <h2>13. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>For questions, concerns, or requests related to this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact:</p>

        <div class="my-6 p-6 bg-zinc-800 border border-zinc-700 rounded-lg">
          <p class="!mb-2"><strong>AUXO Data Labs - Privacy Team</strong></p>
          <p class="!mb-2">Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@auxodata.ae">privacy@auxodata.ae</a></p>
          <p class="!mb-2">General Inquiries: <a href="mailto:hello@auxodata.ae">hello@auxodata.ae</a></p>
          <p class="!mb-2">Location: Dubai, United Arab Emirates</p>
          <p class="!mb-0">Contact Form: <a href={`${base}contact`}>Visit Contact Page</a></p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-8 p-6 bg-lime-400/10 border-l-4 border-lime-400 rounded-r-lg">
          <p class="!mb-0"><strong>Commitment to Privacy:</strong> At AUXO Data Labs, we recognize that trust is the foundation of our client relationships. We are committed to maintaining the highest standards of data protection and transparency in all our operations.</p>
        </div>
      </LegalLayout>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
